        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 2:28PM PDT by NWS Sacramento CA</headline>
        <description>At 226 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Twin Bridges, or 8 miles north of Kirkwood, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Twin Bridges and Sierra At Tahoe.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
